g.text: • Direct proof P → Q is complex or unclear
• Working with negations ¬Q, ¬P is more natural
• Q contains "not" statements or negative conditions
• P involves existence claims that are hard to assume
If n² is odd, then n is odd
If n is even, then n² is even
Since 2k² is an integer, n² = 2m where m = 2k²
